<br>
the military dumps figures in the 100,000 dollar range on training him at their risk without knowing his capability.<br>
<br>
they offer him nearly 100% medical insurance even in rear D to him and his family without knowing his capability.<br>
<br>
they offer him a steady job by contract without knowing his capability.<br>
<br>
the point this man side stepped in his rant was that if ANY OF THEM could be making 70,000 dollars a year *prior* to the army/air force getting a hold of em then they would have took that job and not joined the military.  But they couldnt.  They joined cause it was the best option.  3 hots/cot, some training, a job, a way out of town, a way to grow up  its different for each person but the point remains the same it was their best option.  Their best option was NOT 70,000 dollars a year their best option was the military.  <br>
<br>
Now after the military gets a hold of ya and trains ya you might have some marketable skill but you didnt pay a dime for that transformation.  So for the first term you dont deserve anything resembling more pay.  as i said for the first term you need more grunt details, more training, more discipline.   your pay went to training ya.<br>
<br>
Why i called this rear-d punk a punk was my loyalty to combat arms.   You see he raised tones of patriotism.  The most patriotic people in the military are the relatively civilian skillwise skillless noncom's in combat arms.  who usually hang out because they can give these punks (and we were punks) off the street a fighting chance should they ever go to combat.   People stay in combat arms over 6 years when they could have long ago changed occupations not usually cause they love it but because they feel like they would be letting incoming soldiers down if they left.  Thats a patriot.  But that patriot has no &quot;skills&quot; and gets no respect.<br>
<br>
And what else bothered me bout this letter was that he complained bout going over seas to sit in a fox hole.  THAT WAS MY LIFE FOR 3 YEARS.   So here he is &quot;whine i got to get muddy&quot; when the rest of us stiffs in combat arms lived that 24/7.  My first year in the army i literally spent more time in the field then i did in the rear barracks.  No pointed my skills out in objection.  Forgive me i wont cry cause he has to go man a fox hole. <br>
<br>
 And let me tell you combat arms is always stressfuls.  its like having a boss that gets to push you as FAR as you can go every day.  I got deployed to kuwait once it was actually less stressful then a normal field excercise.   In kuwait people stopped trying to push you and started just trying to pace you.  Instead of getting 4 hours sleep i was getting 7 easy.  <br>
<br>
 And also the army changes alot for soldiers in deployment.   In the rear its very political.  deployed the character of the army changes alot.   It moves to an organization driven by performance instead of rule book standards.   lightening the stress on soldiers by loads as most of em are trained to a fairly high performance standard.  <br>
<br>
As for family and cash?  Deployed soldiers get combat pay + they dont spend any pay.   Families arnt strapped for cash.  families still get to live in the government provided homes.  (ANOTHER BENEFIT!) The check still hits the bank.  There are numerous base faciliaties to help out.  There is a rear D wives structure. (very political but there none the less)  there are councilors to help figure the whole mess out.  if your taxes need done and your wife doesnt know how the army provides people that will do the taxes.  The yard work is done by rear D soldiers.   <br>
<br>
In short.  Give more money to the reenlisted combat arms noncoms  the true patriots. screw everyone else.  TY.<br>
<br>
=)<br>
<br>
<br>
