<br>
This AFIT joker ain't griping about how tough his job is, he's griping about how little money he makes in comparison to Cindy Williams outrageous claims about how overcompensated the military is.<br>
<br>
My dad was in Combat Arms and Combat Support in the USArmy for 24 years, and I know how little money he made and how little we scraped by on. My Dad my 4 times his Army salary after retirement, and his skillset was nowhere near as useful as an IT wonks' is. <br>
<br>
Sure, this low-rank enlisted man doesn't deserve $80k a year, but I don't see him asking for it. I see him wanting to hold his head up and not have to beg the State for food stamps for another month.<br>
<br>
You need a step-ladder to climb off that high horse? <p>a_Bearhat01<br>
