<br>
Serioulsy man, it is emabarassaing to hear you talk this way if you really are/were a service member,  To say that your comrades in arms don't deserve a raise to keep up with the cost of living is sad.  As it is, raises were always a joke, 10% looks good on paper, but when your base salary is 10k, its not that big of  a deal.  Hell I never even remember getting a 10% raises, was more like 4 or 5%.<br>
<br>
I was a E5 in the Navy when I got out to go to college and my Base salary was maybe 18k, and now with graduation coming up in May, I'm prolly gonna join back up as an Ensign, and then my base salary will prolly bump up to 28k.  My degree is Nursing, and currently I can make 50K starting anywhere in my state with this degree...are you saying that once I join, I'm going to be paid too much?<br>
<br>
People don't join the service to make a buck, they join to serve their contry, whether they are a grunt or an admin desk jockey....  Because of them there is no draft and everyone else can rest assured THEY don't have to if they don't want to.  These people should be respected for their sarcifices, not punished.<br>
