<br>
What the &quot;punk&quot; is doing is taking is opportunity for granted and/or trying to downplay that he got something he wanted.<br>
<br>
The myth being perpetrated here is that the soul reason soldiers enlist is out of patriotism and duty.   90% or more can point to something they wanted.  education benefits/ a secure job/a way out of town/ security for their family/ a way to grow up/pay off their secure loan.  They got that. what ever it was they were looking for they got.  for me it was a way out of town.  they got whatever they were looking for and alot more.  it was the deal; the deal was fulfilled.   practically speaking very few enlisted people joined cause they wanted to serve without there being another reason.<br>
<br>
single soldier first term enlisted make enough money.  they have disposable income of 25 bucks a day.  no rent. no bills. no medical. no food expenses.  if you just chill out during the week spend 5 bucks on whatever by the end of the week you blow 150 bucks every weekend.  this is the bottom rung soldier.  Single that has avoided serious bills.    this is a soldier excepted without question bout ability bout drive bout anything.  sign lets go. <br>
<br>
its enough.  what might not be enough is reenlisted pays which primairly are career e4s and e5s+ and housing pay where applicable.<br>
  <br>
<br>
<br>
as for the combat arms thing.   there is nothing specially grueling bout these deployments specially these 3 to 6 month missions.  if they  werent doing that they would be in the field doing the same stuff only with less sleep.   75% of the time our rear support further up then our battalion aid wouldnt go with us only a few major field excercises that rolled out brigade/division assets.   <br>
<br>
as for the difference live bullets being shot at you makes.  Theres no pay for compensating live bullets.  theres no number.<br>
